HEADWORD: Disembodied
<hw>Dis`em*bod"ied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Divested of a
body; ceased to be corporal; incorporeal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>disembodied</qex> spirits of the dead.</q>
<rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disembodiment</ent>⟦br⟧
